CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 25, 1958, pg. A14, reads: "January Bride and Groom - Miss Marva Regina Reeves, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Hezekiah Reeves of Thompson St., East End, became the bride of Marion pg. Kimes, son of Mr. and Mrs. Charity Kimes of Petersburg, Tenn. The Jan 18 wedding took place at the D'Equesta Dining Room, Fifth Ave.  Juanita R. Mitchell, sister of the bride, and Jack Woodford were attendants. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Groom Marion P. Kimes wearing striped tie, and bride Marva Regina Reeves Kimes, posed in D'Equesta Dining Room
